[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scottish man dies while swimming in Bali

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 42-year-old man from Scotland has died after a swimming accident on Bali.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Vishal Chopra, an accountant from Glasgow, is believed to have been on the Indonesian island to attend a family wedding.
He reportedly died after getting into difficulty while swimming offshore.
The Foreign and Commonwealth Office said: "We are supporting the family of a British national who has died in Bali, and have provided bereavement information at this difficult time."
